hurricane hunter robert sheets, who has flown into the eye of more than 200 of the violent storms, has been named director of the national hurricane center
the job makes him responsible for warning the 40 million coastal residents from texas to maine about the onslaught of a tropical storm, one of nature's most destructive and powerful weather systems
his first-hand experience inside hurricanes, gained over 16 years as a researcher, will be a valuable, he said. ``i know as much about hurricane structure and their variations as anyone.''
